A pseudosarcoma of the duodenum. Pseudosarcoma is a rare malignant neoplasm composed of both carcinomatous and sarcomatous elements. It occurs most frequently in the uterus. When located in the gastrointestinal tract the lethality is almost 100% one year after the diagnosis. Clinical observations and radiological findings in a 52-year old patient with pseudosarcoma of the duodenum are presented in this report.